                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240603-210-victim1796 t18240603-210-viclabel1091"></join>, and live in Westminster - the prisoner and I lodged together for about a month, and I lent him my clothes now and then. I had lent him a coat and some other things, and this handkerchief was with some things on the bureau bedstead - he said one evening that he was going to receive 2000 l. the next morning, and he should lie in bed in until seven o'clock. I got up about five; he then said</p>
               <p>"Wait at the door, and I will go with you." I waited to see if he was coming, and he ran away. I had lent him all these things except the handkerchief. The constable took the handkerchief off his neck at Bow-street.</p>
